cru.borda <-  read.table("http://www.leg.ufpr.br/geoR/tutorials/datasets/Cruciani.border", head=T)[,2:3]
cru.borda <- rbind(cru.borda, cru.borda[1,])

## plot
plot(cru, bord = cru.borda)

args(plot.geodata)
## function (x, coords = x$coords, data = x$data, borders = x$borders, 
##     trend = "cte", lambda = 1, col.data = 1, weights.divide = "units.m", 
##     lowess = FALSE, scatter3d = FALSE, density = TRUE, rug = TRUE, 
##     qt.col, ...) 
## NULL

hist(cru$data, main="", xlab="K")

hist(log(cru$data), main="", xlab="log(K)")

## points
points(cru, bord=cru.borda)

args(points.geodata)
## function (x, coords = x$coords, data = x$data, data.col = 1, 
##     borders = x$borders, pt.divide = c("data.proportional", "rank.proportional", 
##         "quintiles", "quartiles", "deciles", "equal"), lambda = 1, 
##     trend = "cte", abs.residuals = FALSE, weights.divide = "units.m", 
##     cex.min, cex.max, cex.var, pch.seq, col.seq, add.to.plot = FALSE,

##     permute = FALSE, ...)

args(variog)
## function (geodata, coords = geodata$coords, data = geodata$data, 
##     uvec = "default", breaks = "default", trend = "cte", lambda = 1, 
##     option = c("bin", "cloud", "smooth"), estimator.type = c("classical", 
##         "modulus"), nugget.tolerance, max.dist, pairs.min = 2, 
##     bin.cloud = FALSE, direction = "omnidirectional", tolerance = pi/8, 
##     unit.angle = c("radians", "degrees"), angles = FALSE, messages, 
##     ...) 
## NULL
cru.cl1 <- variog(cru, option = "cloud")
## variog: computing omnidirectional variogram
plot(cru.cl1)

cru.v2 <- variog(cru, lambda = 0)
## variog: computing omnidirectional variogram
plot(cru.v2)

cru.cl2 <- variog(cru, lambda = 0, option = "cloud")
## variog: computing omnidirectional variogram
plot(cru.cl2)

cru.v3 <- variog(cru, lambda = 0, max.dist=9)
## variog: computing omnidirectional variogram
plot(cru.v3)

cru.v4 <- variog(cru, lambda = 0, uvec=seq(0,9,l=8))
## variog: computing omnidirectional variogram
plot(cru.v4)

cru.v5 <- variog(cru, lambda = 0, uvec=seq(0,12,l=8))
## variog: computing omnidirectional variogram
plot(cru.v5)

cru.v6 <- variog(cru, lambda = 0, uvec=seq(0,15,l=8))
## variog: computing omnidirectional variogram
plot(cru.v6)

cru.v <- variog(cru, lambda = 0, uvec=seq(0,9,l=8), bin.cl=T)
## variog: computing omnidirectional variogram
plot(cru.v)

plot(cru.v, bin.cloud = T)

cru.mv <- variog(cru, lambda = 0, uvec=seq(0,9,l=8), est="mod")
## variog: computing omnidirectional variogram
plot(cru.mv)

cru.v <- variog(cru, lambda = 0, uvec=seq(0,9,l=8), bin.cl=T)
## variog: computing omnidirectional variogram
cru.env <- variog.mc.env(cru, obj.variog = cru.v)
## variog.env: generating 99 simulations by permutating data values
## variog.env: computing the empirical variogram for the 99 simulations
## variog.env: computing the envelops
plot(cru.v, env = cru.env)
